txt.en: 'What was that sound?'
'I fear that I will meet my death, by Orc or by this hole in my heart.'
'Bah! I will shake off such sobering thoughts for now.'
'When the Orcs come, I want you to help my men, [placeholder].'
'Wynmar must wake from his dream before the Orcs come....'
'I want them to run for Stangard. I will keep the Orcs' attention here, on me.'
'I have never seen a man so taken by a lady, [placeholder].'
'Hopefully we can all escape safely back to our own land!'
'Where is their leader?'
'I hope you can help me rouse him before the attack....'
'He will not be pleased that we are cutting down his minions.'
'Wynmar.'
'I want you all to make for Stangard at once. Leave me to face the leader alone.'
'Wynmar!'
'The attacks will not cease until we take him down, but you are not soldiers.'
'Hm? What is it, Rothulf?'
'For the last time, you great oaf: Orcs are coming for us!'
'You must forget the Elf-girl; stand and fight!'
'Yes... I suppose I must, Rothulf.'
'You cannot stop the Orcs. We will wipe out the horse-men and all who interfere!'
'Fool! The Orcs will come....'
'Victory is near! I can sense it!'

'Wynmar, look out!'
